---
name: v21-native-effect-one-shot-violation
---

# One-shot resumption rejection

The outer print is a suffix: it must not run after the second invocation of the
plain effect's continuation is rejected.

```scalascript
effect One:
  def op(): Int

val result = handle(One.op()) {
  case One.op(resume) => resume(1) + resume(2)
}
println(s"suffix: $result")
```
